title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.3: MATERNAL AND NEWBORN HEALTH

description.narrative: Output 1.3: National and county levels have technical and managerial capacity to provide newborn, child and maternal health services (UNDAF output 3.1.1), which contributes to Child Health, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: By 2019, children, adolescents and women, especially in the most vulnerable and hard-to-reach areas, including those in emergencies, utilize high impact evidence-based quality essential health services.

description.narrative: By October 2019, the policy on Focused Antenatal Care had been developed and adapted and is currently being implemented nationwide. Some 90% of pregnant women had received IPT2, far exceeding the annual target of 60%. Institutional deliveries also increased from the 2018 baseline value of 51% to 53%, while births attended by a skilled attendant also improved from 50% in 2018 to 52% in October 2019. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
